column34: I think it's pretty cool that this survey is being conducted. The TED talk was brilliant. However I can't help but feel like Mines culture somehow inhibits the flourishing of a healthy sex culture. Maybe it's just the kind of people here or the demanding workload, but when one thinks of sex as it pertains to Mines as compared to most other colleges it comes an air of underdevelopment. I wouldn't go quite so far as to compare it to High School-esque sexual oppression, but it's somewhere on the spectrum. Everyone likes sex, and when responsible its benefits are enormous; particularly in such a high stress environment as Mines. So perhaps all Mines needs is a little nurturing when it comes to sex culture and things could be very different in a good way. ....Or maybe I'm just a dweeb that never gets laid, who fuckin knows?
